          </Citation>
          <Comment>This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Leu1324Glnfs*75) in the COL7A1 gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in COL7A1 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 16971478). This variant is not present in population databases (gnomAD no frequency). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with COL7A1-related conditions. ClinVar contains an entry for this variant (Variation ID: 291012). For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
